    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1978-02-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1978-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="141"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d141">
                <head>141. Letter From President <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName> to
                    Multiple Recipients<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d141fn1">Source: Carter
                        Library, Office of the Chief of Staff, <persName corresp="#p_JH_1">Hamilton
                            Jordan</persName>’s Confidential Files, Box 36, Panama Canal Treaty
                        1978. No classification marking. Sent to <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1"
                            >Vance</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BGS_1">Brown</persName>,
                            <persName corresp="#p_BZK_1">Brzezinski</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_JH_1">Jordan</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_MF_2"
                            >Moore</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1978-02-07">February 7, 1978</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>To <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Cy</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_PHR_1">Harold</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BZK_1"
                            >Zbig</persName>, Ham, <persName corresp="#p_CF_1">Frank</persName>
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>In my calls &amp; meetings with Senators I’ve found that we are being hurt by
                    varying answers to canal maintenance and operations cost questions.</p>
                <p>Please consult immediately &amp; evolve a clear procedure for answering new
                    questions and for giving to me &amp; others existing and future information.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Jimmy</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
